Content:
"fmt2" is <i>supposed</i> to contain a format string. It's supposed to contain the format string from "fmt". That's how it prints the args from "ap".<p>The bug is when getprogname() also returns a string containing a format specifier (e.g. "%s"), which is not expected.<p>Clearly the fix is:<p><pre><code>  fprintf(stderr, "%s: ", getprogname());
  va_start(ap, fmt);
  vfprintf(stderr, fmt, ap);
  va_end(ap);
  fprintf(stderr, "\n");
</code></pre>
(Edit for formatting, clarity)
